best move. However, it makes the position unbalanced and creates problems for
black)} g6 $6 {(Black makes a mistake right away! It often happens when you
pressure an opponent)} 10. h4 {(After the black's move g6 white got some real
attacking chances.)} h6 11. Qd2 $1 {(a very interesting and creative idea!)}
Bg7 12. Qh2 {(White wants to attack the black's queen-side weaknesses also.
