is not a threat, white should keep attacking!)} 25. g5 $1 {(A positional
sacrifice of a pawn is a pretty standard way to open lines and diagonals for
your pieces. Such sacrifices are nearly always correct.)} Rh8 (25... hxg5 $2
26. Bxg6+ Kxg6 27. Qh5+ Kf5 28. Qf7+ $18) 26. Bxg6+ Kf8 27. Nf6 {(we should go
forward!)} Ke7 (27... Bxf6 28. gxf6 Qxf6 29. d5 {! a counterblow}) 28. Rxc6
bxc6 29. Qxe5+ Kf8 {(All the black's pieces are on the last rank and white
will win easily in all the variations)} 30. Qf4 Ke7 31. Nh7 Rxh7 32. Qf7+ Kd6
33. Bxh7 Qxg5 34. Rg1 Be6 35. Rxg5 {White wins} 1-0

